to want to be a waitress. . .

777
00:52:20,070 --> 00:52:21,140
. . .for the rest of your life.

778
00:52:21,390 --> 00:52:22,870
l am studying to be an actress.

779
00:52:23,110 --> 00:52:25,020
-You told me.
-Well, l am.

780
00:52:29,670 --> 00:52:31,310
This is for you. . .

781
00:52:31,550 --> 00:52:33,820
. . .your father. . .

782
00:52:34,190 --> 00:52:36,220
. . .and your acting career.

783
00:52:37,870 --> 00:52:39,780
Please take it and l'll go.

784
00:52:46,470 --> 00:52:48,380
$1 00,000.

785
00:52:53,830 --> 00:52:55,420
We don't need your money.

786
00:52:56,070 --> 00:52:57,790
Linda, it'll help you.

787
00:52:57,990 --> 00:53:00,020
Look what it's done for you.

788
00:53:00,230 --> 00:53:03,030
Tell your story walking,
before l call a cop!

789
00:53:03,230 --> 00:53:05,020
Get out of here!

790
00:53:08,710 --> 00:53:10,140
Closet.

791
00:53:15,510 --> 00:53:17,020
l know.

792
00:53:33,990 --> 00:53:35,580
Want to take her for a spin, Hobson?

793
00:53:36,030 --> 00:53:37,510
No, thank you, Arthur.

794
00:53:38,430 --> 00:53:41,390
Mr. Bach, be sure you call me
anytime you need the track.

795
00:53:41,630 --> 00:53:43,620
-Take it easy.
-Thank you.

796
00:53:49,990 --> 00:53:51,420
Do you know how miserable l am?

797
00:53:51,630 --> 00:53:55,420
You're miserable?
l've got all this and l'm on a salary.

798
00:53:55,670 --> 00:53:57,390
ARTHUR 3

799
00:54:01,390 --> 00:54:04,300
Do you know the worst part?
The worst part of being me?

800
00:54:04,550 --> 00:54:06,620
l should imagine your breath.

801
00:54:07,270 --> 00:54:09,420
Let me be unhappy, will you?

802
00:54:10,310 --> 00:54:11,900
You know, Hobson. . .

803
00:54:12,910 --> 00:54:15,100
. . .l could love somebody.

804
00:54:16,110 --> 00:54:17,620
l never got to love anybody!

805
00:54:18,790 --> 00:54:23,140
What do l have to live for?
l'm a failure. l'm just in the way.

806
00:54:23,470 --> 00:54:25,460
Would you remove your helmet, please?

807
00:54:25,670 --> 00:54:27,420
-Why?
-Please.

808
00:54:31,710 --> 00:54:32,860
Thank you.

809
00:54:33,110 --> 00:54:34,180
Now your goggles.

810
00:54:34,430 --> 00:54:36,220
-Why?
-Please.

811
00:54:41,590 --> 00:54:43,230
You spoiled little bastard!

812
00:54:43,750 --> 00:54:47,220
You're a man who has everything.
But that's not enough.

813
00:54:47,470 --> 00:54:51,220
You feel unloved? Welcome to
the world. Everyone is unloved!

814
00:54:52,270 --> 00:54:55,700
Stop feeling sorry for yourself.
And incidentally, l love you.

815
00:54:56,430 --> 00:54:58,660
Marry Susan, Arthur.

816
00:54:59,470 --> 00:55:02,620
Poor drunks do not find love.

817
00:55:03,270 --> 00:55:06,860
Poor drunks have very few teeth.
They urinate outdoors.

818
00:55:07,110 --> 00:55:09,180
They freeze to death in summer.

819
00:55:09,510 --> 00:55:11,260
l can't bear to think
of you that way.

820
00:55:11,510 --> 00:55:13,150
l need Linda, Hobson.

821
00:55:13,390 --> 00:55:14,500
l see.

822
00:55:15,110 --> 00:55:17,860
Well, perhaps fate
will lend a hand, Arthur.

823
00:55:18,510 --> 00:55:20,070
One never knows.

824
00:55:22,470 --> 00:55:23,740
Good afternoon?

825
00:55:24,270 --> 00:55:25,830
May l come in?

826
00:55:26,510 --> 00:55:29,820
lf you and your undershirt
would walk two paces backwards. . .

827
00:55:30,150 --> 00:55:31,740
. . .l could enter this dwelling.

828
00:55:51,630 --> 00:55:53,380
How revolting.

829
00:55:57,830 --> 00:56:00,820
Look who's here.
The British Tonto.

830
00:56:01,510 --> 00:56:03,260
How are you? How's Arthur?

831
00:56:03,670 --> 00:56:05,940
Ever since l met Arthur,
l liked him.

832
00:56:06,190 --> 00:56:09,500
We have to make sure these
two wonderful kids stay together.

833
00:56:09,710 --> 00:56:10,780
Who is this person?

834
00:56:12,150 --> 00:56:14,950
-He's my father.
-Yes, and l'd like to say that--

835
00:56:15,150 --> 00:56:16,420
Try not to speak.

836
00:56:16,630 --> 00:56:19,510
Would you get me a cup of tea?
l wish to speak to Linda.

837
00:56:20,070 --> 00:56:21,420
Sure.

838
00:56:23,710 --> 00:56:26,140
There is an engagement
party tonight. . .

839
00:56:26,390 --> 00:56:29,220
. . .at Arthur's father's house
in Southampton.

840
00:56:29,670 --> 00:56:32,630
Here is the address.
Perhaps you should attend.

841
00:56:33,030 --> 00:56:34,750
Are all the ones
he passed up coming?

842
00:56:34,950 --> 00:56:37,060
Young woman, this is a tie
you cannot steal!

843
00:56:37,310 --> 00:56:39,380
This is a tie you'll have
to work for.

844
00:56:39,630 --> 00:56:42,900
Are you inviting me
to Arthur's engagement party?

845
00:56:43,110 --> 00:56:45,220
This is not an invitation.

846
00:56:45,510 --> 00:56:46,830
However. . .

847
00:56:47,230 --> 00:56:50,500
. . .if there's one thing that
old gentlemen can still do. . .

848
00:56:50,750 --> 00:56:53,900
. . .they can still spot
young gentlemen in love.

849
00:56:55,070 --> 00:56:57,020
Please go to the party.

850
00:56:57,670 --> 00:56:58,820
Are you all right?

851
00:56:59,030 --> 00:57:00,860
Yes, l'm fine.

852
00:57:08,150 --> 00:57:09,660
Does Arthur know you're here?

853
00:57:09,910 --> 00:57:12,980
No, Arthur is far too fine
a person to be involved. . .

854
00:57:13,230 --> 00:57:15,380
. . .in something as devious as this.

855
00:57:16,110 --> 00:57:18,420
You really look out for him,
don't you?

856
00:57:18,870 --> 00:57:22,300
And it is a job
that l recommend highly.

857
00:57:23,750 --> 00:57:24,900
l have something for you.

858
00:57:25,110 --> 00:57:25,940
For me?

859
00:57:33,190 --> 00:57:34,340
What is it?

860
00:57:34,590 --> 00:57:37,230
lf l told you,
it would spoil the surprise.

861
00:57:37,430 --> 00:57:38,940
Don't open it.

862
00:57:40,070 --> 00:57:41,060
Here's your tea.

863
00:57:41,310 --> 00:57:43,220
l despise tea.

864
00:57:43,430 --> 00:57:45,620
Would you bring me 2 aspirin
from the bathroom?

865
00:57:45,870 --> 00:57:50,380
You'll find them on the top shelf,
behind the untouched shaving cream.

866
00:58:02,350 --> 00:58:04,340
That sounds bad.
Have you seen a doctor?

867
00:58:05,270 --> 00:58:07,020
Yes.

868
00:58:07,230 --> 00:58:09,020
And he has seen me.

869
00:58:13,470 --> 00:58:14,950
You know. . .

870
00:58:17,310 --> 00:58:19,460
. . .l think Arthur has
a very good friend.

871
00:58:22,190 --> 00:58:23,620
May l kiss you on the cheek?

872
00:58:23,910 --> 00:58:25,820
ls it something you feel
strongly about?

873
00:58:34,870 --> 00:58:36,380
What about your aspirins?

874
00:58:37,030 --> 00:58:39,420
The aspirins are for you, my dear.

875
00:59:59,550 --> 01:00:00,500
Hello.

876
01:00:02,310 --> 01:00:03,580
Good evening.

877
01:00:12,390 --> 01:00:14,500
God knows when l'll see you again.

878
01:00:14,950 --> 01:00:17,460
Arthur, will you play
something for us?

879
01:00:41,390 --> 01:00:44,350
-Don't you hate these things?
-Despise them.

880
01:00:44,550 --> 01:00:46,460
Actually, seriously. . .

881
01:00:47,470 --> 01:00:49,780
. . .songs come and go.

882
01:00:50,070 --> 01:00:52,420
But l love the classics.

883
01:00:52,870 --> 01:00:54,780
And l hope you'll enjoy this one.

884
01:01:06,790 --> 01:01:08,380
You'd better watch out

885
01:01:09,590 --> 01:01:11,420
You'd better not cry

886
01:01:11,910 --> 01:01:14,100
Are you good friends with Arthur?

887
01:01:14,430 --> 01:01:15,910
For ages.

888
01:01:16,150 --> 01:01:20,060
l'm so pleased he finally found
the right woman. Where is she?

889
01:01:20,950 --> 01:01:21,740
Over there.

890
01:01:21,950 --> 01:01:23,860
lsn't she just beautiful?

891
01:01:24,110 --> 01:01:25,060
Of course she is.

892
01:01:25,630 --> 01:01:27,540
Why would Arthur marry a dog?

893
01:01:27,750 --> 01:01:28,620
Pardon?

894
01:01:28,830 --> 01:01:31,140
Santa Claus is coming to town

895
01:01:35,510 --> 01:01:37,820
How does it feel to be
getting married?

896
01:01:38,950 --> 01:01:40,270
Blue Moon

897
01:01:41,390 --> 01:01:43,460
You saw me standing alone

898
01:01:45,150 --> 01:01:47,220
Without a dream in my heart

899
01:01:49,830 --> 01:01:52,180
Thanks a lot. That's flattering.

900
01:01:52,750 --> 01:01:55,220
lf you knew Susan
Like l knew Susan

901
01:01:57,670 --> 01:01:59,150
l need a drink!

902
01:02:04,390 --> 01:02:07,660
-Tell me your entire name, darling.
-Preston Langly.

903
01:02:08,510 --> 01:02:12,180
Really! lf you don't remember
when we met, l mean, honestly!

904
01:02:12,430 --> 01:02:14,740
-Put your arm around me.
-Of course.

905
01:02:17,510 --> 01:02:19,100
Linda, you're here.

906
01:02:20,630 --> 01:02:21,620
So true.

907
01:02:23,550 --> 01:02:24,740
Join us.

908
01:02:27,910 --> 01:02:30,060
Congratulations.
Father sends his regards.

909
01:02:30,310 --> 01:02:32,420
-Does he?
-Yes, he does.

910
01:02:32,870 --> 01:02:35,140
Wednesday night may be
difficult for me.

911
01:02:35,390 --> 01:02:38,060
-What?
-You're looking wonderful, my dear.

912
01:02:38,310 --> 01:02:40,180
-Aren't l? Thank you.
-Wednesday?

913
01:02:40,430 --> 01:02:42,740
lt's difficult for her
that night, Preston.

914
01:02:42,990 --> 01:02:46,380
lsn't that the night you usually
attend the ballet, darling?

915
01:02:46,630 --> 01:02:50,260
Actually, l feel foolish,
but l don't recall ever making--

916
01:02:50,510 --> 01:02:53,980
Would you be divine and
get me a gin and tonic?

917
01:02:54,750 --> 01:02:56,660
Scotch for me, Preston.

918
01:02:57,870 --> 01:03:01,060
-You wait here for me?
-lf it takes forever.

919
01:03:09,910 --> 01:03:12,380
What are you doing here. . .

920
01:03:12,630 --> 01:03:14,940
. . .and why are you talking like that?

921
01:03:17,990 --> 01:03:19,710
l was in the neighborhood.

922
01:03:19,950 --> 01:03:22,540
lt took me two buses,
three cabs and a train. . .

923
01:03:22,790 --> 01:03:25,510
. . .to get into the neighborhood.
But what the hell?

924
01:03:26,190 --> 01:03:29,070
Nice place. l like a living room
you can land a plane in.

925
01:03:29,310 --> 01:03:31,870
There's more of it. You like a tour?

926
01:03:32,590 --> 01:03:34,460
l've seen bedrooms.

927
01:03:34,710 --> 01:03:36,700
Don't be a lover. Be a person.

928
01:03:37,950 --> 01:03:39,620
Make me happy.

929
01:03:40,230 --> 01:03:42,500
Her name is Linda Marolla.

930
01:03:42,870 --> 01:03:46,750
She's the one Arthur saw
the other night. She lives in Queens.

931
01:04:03,270 --> 01:04:04,260
Mario, please!

932
01:04:04,470 --> 01:04:08,460
Don't worry. l talked to the warden.
We'll get you out of here.

933
01:04:08,710 --> 01:04:12,990
When l was a kid, l used to open
their stalls and let them run out.

934
01:04:13,230 --> 01:04:15,660
You should have been there
the day l freed my goldfish.

935
01:04:15,910 --> 01:04:18,100
Come over here.
l want you two to meet.

936
01:04:18,350 --> 01:04:21,420
Pancho, this is Linda.
l told you about her, remember?

937
01:04:23,790 --> 01:04:26,260
lt must have been something,
growing up with all this.

938
01:04:26,470 --> 01:04:28,540
l was away at boarding school
most of the time.

939
01:04:28,870 --> 01:04:32,750
l was kicked out of ten prep schools.
l was a bad kid.

940
01:04:33,150 --> 01:04:34,470
No, you weren't.

941
01:04:34,830 --> 01:04:36,660
You just wanted to go home.

942
01:04:37,550 --> 01:04:39,700
Bad kids don't grow up
as nice as you.

943
01:04:39,950 --> 01:04:42,460
-Why do you think Pancho loves you?
-Thank you.

944
01:04:45,190 --> 01:04:47,460
This is kind of like prom night,
isn't it?

945
01:04:48,750 --> 01:04:50,660
l mean, we're all dressed up.

946
01:04:54,950 --> 01:04:56,270
Have you ever been in love?

947
01:04:59,070 --> 01:05:00,020
You?

948
01:05:02,710 --> 01:05:05,860
But when l was little,
l thought the moon followed me.

949
01:05:06,110 --> 01:05:06,900
What?

950
01:05:09,070 --> 01:05:13,190
l would walk and l thought
the moon went anyplace l did.

951
01:05:14,790 --> 01:05:16,220
That's great!

952
01:05:17,030 --> 01:05:19,380
l know it's silly,
but l was only eight years old.

953
01:05:20,750 --> 01:05:23,860
l thought it meant something special
would happen to me someday.

954
01:05:24,230 --> 01:05:27,980
So l've been waiting. Every day l've
been doing my hair, and washing. . .

955
01:05:28,870 --> 01:05:30,780
-. . .my face--
-Can l kiss you?

956
01:05:31,310 --> 01:05:32,630
Please.

957
01:05:42,150 --> 01:05:43,900
l wasn't talking to you.

958
01:05:46,070 --> 01:05:49,860
Why is it you can make me laugh
at the saddest times in my life?

959
01:05:50,110 --> 01:05:51,700
l'm funny, that's why.

960
01:05:51,990 --> 01:05:53,020
l'm funny!

961
01:05:53,990 --> 01:05:55,100
Yeah, that's it.

962
01:05:56,070 --> 01:05:57,630
You're going to marry Susan.

963
01:05:59,670 --> 01:06:03,260
l'm still glad l came here.
Made a fool out of myself.

964
01:06:03,990 --> 01:06:05,420
l wish we had made love.

965
01:06:07,430 --> 01:06:09,740
l'd give anything
to see you in the morning.

966
01:06:11,070 --> 01:06:14,740
l have to marry Susan.
lf l don't, my family will cut me off.

967
01:06:14,990 --> 01:06:17,020
lt's almost a billion dollars.

968
01:06:19,230 --> 01:06:21,220
One of the horses just fainted.

969
01:06:23,270 --> 01:06:24,780
Look, this is ridiculous.

970
01:06:25,030 --> 01:06:28,660
You got cab fare to the city?
l don't like the train at night.

971
01:06:30,150 --> 01:06:31,980
Look, when Susan and l
get married. . .

972
01:06:32,230 --> 01:06:34,870
. . .l can set you up in an apartment
and we can--

973
01:06:35,110 --> 01:06:36,260
Forget it.

974
01:06:38,310 --> 01:06:39,340
Are you cute!

975
01:06:44,590 --> 01:06:46,700
l thought l'd find you here.

976
01:06:47,110 --> 01:06:49,580
He just loves that smelly old horse.

977
01:06:49,830 --> 01:06:50,660
Have we met?

978
01:06:52,190 --> 01:06:53,860
l don't think you have.

979
01:06:54,070 --> 01:06:56,870
Linda Marolla,
this is Susan Johnson, my fiance.

980
01:06:57,470 --> 01:06:59,340
l hope l'm not interrupting.

981
01:06:59,950 --> 01:07:01,860
l'd say that if l were you.

982
01:07:02,510 --> 01:07:04,860
We might as well tell her.

983
01:07:06,150 --> 01:07:07,630
You tell her.

984
01:07:10,910 --> 01:07:14,950
My husband, Harold,
went to prep school with Arthur.

985
01:07:15,830 --> 01:07:18,500
Harold lost a fortune gambling.
He's sick!

986
01:07:18,790 --> 01:07:19,860
He's a sick man!

987
01:07:20,550 --> 01:07:22,460
But he's my husband.

988
01:07:23,270 --> 01:07:26,070
l'm not one of your guests.
l came for one reason.

989
01:07:26,310 --> 01:07:29,460
l came here to beg Arthur
to lend us some money.

990
01:07:30,750 --> 01:07:32,100
One of my kids. . .

991
01:07:32,350 --> 01:07:34,460
. . .my youngest, my baby. . .

992
01:07:34,750 --> 01:07:36,540
. . .needs an operation.

993
01:07:37,150 --> 01:07:40,110
Harold hasn't kept up the insurance.
l don't know where to turn!

994
01:07:40,350 --> 01:07:41,860
Do l have to go on?

995
01:07:42,110 --> 01:07:43,180
No, of course not!

996
01:07:43,430 --> 01:07:45,300
Of course not!

997
01:07:45,550 --> 01:07:48,380
-Arthur, l wasn't spying on you.
-l know that!

998
01:07:48,630 --> 01:07:51,660
There's an urgent phone call
for you from Bitterman.

999
01:07:52,150 --> 01:07:53,020
Thank you.

1000
01:07:55,470 --> 01:07:57,460
Say hello to Harold for me.

1001
01:08:08,950 --> 01:08:10,460
You all right, Bitterman?

1002
01:08:10,750 --> 01:08:11,860
Yes, sir.

1003
01:08:14,670 --> 01:08:17,060
Would you like me to get you
some Scotch, sir?

1004
01:08:17,910 --> 01:08:19,700
We'll get through this together.

1005
01:08:24,870 --> 01:08:26,460
lt's very hard.

1006
01:08:30,030 --> 01:08:32,060
l'm glad to have you here, sir.

1007
01:08:34,150 --> 01:08:36,870
Bitterman, do me a favor.

1008
01:08:37,390 --> 01:08:38,950
Go back to the house.

1009
01:08:39,310 --> 01:08:43,350
Phone my father and Mr. Johnson and
Miss Susan. Tell them what's happened.

1010
01:08:43,590 --> 01:08:47,260
The wedding will have to wait.
And bring me back some clothes here.

1011
01:08:57,230 --> 01:08:59,500
Okay, let's open the presents.

1012
01:09:00,550 --> 01:09:01,740
l'm sorry, Arthur.

1013
01:09:02,670 --> 01:09:05,180
-For what?
-For leaving you.

1014
01:09:07,270 --> 01:09:08,670
You're not leaving anyone.

1015
01:09:14,150 --> 01:09:16,380
Why, it's a basketball!

1016
01:09:17,350 --> 01:09:19,860
What the hell?
l knew you didn't have one.

1017
01:09:20,470 --> 01:09:22,900
lf l feel the urge to dribble. . .

1018
01:09:23,150 --> 01:09:24,940
. . .l can always call the nurse.

1019
01:09:26,150 --> 01:09:27,870
l'll put this over here.

1020
01:09:33,150 --> 01:09:35,740
You purchased a choo-choo?

1021
01:09:36,030 --> 01:09:37,860
Look, the wheels go round.

1022
01:09:44,710 --> 01:09:46,380
l'm very pleased.

1023
01:09:46,630 --> 01:09:48,060
Do you remember. . .

1024
01:09:48,270 --> 01:09:51,820
. . .when you used to play
hide-and-seek with me?

1025
01:09:52,070 --> 01:09:54,020
l used to hide and
you never found me!

1026
01:09:54,670 --> 01:09:57,390
-Did you know l never looked?
-Come on!

1027
01:09:57,870 --> 01:10:00,590
Well, l looked a little.

1028
01:10:02,830 --> 01:10:04,660
One for you, one for me.
Put it on.

1029
01:10:06,150 --> 01:10:08,060
l don't wish to put it on.

1030
01:10:13,390 --> 01:10:14,950
l'll put it on.

1031
01:10:19,630 --> 01:10:23,460
lf l begin to die,
please take this off my head.

1032
01:10:23,750 --> 01:10:25,860
This isn't how
l wish to be remembered.

1033
01:10:28,590 --> 01:10:29,860
Aren't they great?

1034
01:10:33,190 --> 01:10:35,620
l've got guns and
holsters too. Look.

1035
01:10:38,150 --> 01:10:40,870
Just in town for supplies, partner.

1036
01:10:43,670 --> 01:10:45,020
Arthur, l'm frightened.

1037
01:10:49,950 --> 01:10:51,860
l know you're frightened.

1038
01:10:52,510 --> 01:10:54,460
l'm going to take care of you.

1039
01:11:26,070 --> 01:11:27,500
Good morning, Mr. Bach.

1040
01:11:27,750 --> 01:11:28,860
Hi, Ken.

1041
01:11:35,230 --> 01:11:36,950
Here, l'll take that.

1042
01:11:37,190 --> 01:11:40,460
You look terrible.
You haven't slept in a week.

1043
01:11:40,830 --> 01:11:43,100
Well, we had a bad night.
He was up.

1044
01:11:43,310 --> 01:11:45,980
l got the kippers and eggs.
l'll get fired.

1045
01:11:46,230 --> 01:11:48,420
No, you won't.

1046
01:11:49,030 --> 01:11:50,020
Listen.

1047
01:11:50,670 --> 01:11:51,900
For lunch. . .

1048
01:11:53,830 --> 01:11:57,660
. . .l want the trout almondine
from Lutce. Tell Henri it's for me.

1049
01:11:57,870 --> 01:11:59,060
He shouldn't eat that.

1050
01:11:59,270 --> 01:12:02,100
l don't want his last meal
to be Jell-O.

1051
01:12:02,350 --> 01:12:04,460
Thanks very much. See you later.

1052
01:12:07,110 --> 01:12:08,540
Look who's up.

1053
01:12:12,550 --> 01:12:14,660
We have eggs, we have kippers.

1054
01:12:14,910 --> 01:12:17,500
We have croissants.
We have a yellow rose.

1055
01:12:17,830 --> 01:12:21,340
We have strawberries.
We have blueberry cakes.

1056
01:12:21,590 --> 01:12:24,230
We have orange juice
and great coffee.

1057
01:12:25,190 --> 01:12:27,100
Right. Table for one, sir.

1058
01:12:27,750 --> 01:12:29,020
Your regular.

1059
01:12:31,190 --> 01:12:32,620
You know, Arthur. . .

1060
01:12:33,870 --> 01:12:35,460
. . .l'm very glad you're here.

1061
01:12:35,910 --> 01:12:38,580
l want you to eat this.
This is costing me.

1062
01:12:38,830 --> 01:12:42,220
l've got chefs working at six
in the morning all over town.

1063
01:12:42,470 --> 01:12:44,220
You look awful.

1064
01:12:44,510 --> 01:12:47,860
That's because you've never
seen me sober. Now eat.

1065
01:12:48,070 --> 01:12:50,300
Come on. You used to make me eat.

1066
01:12:56,430 --> 01:12:58,150
lt's not so bad.

1067
01:12:58,790 --> 01:13:01,260
You don't need to be
so frightened about it.

1068
01:13:03,110 --> 01:13:05,340
-What?
-Dying.

1069
01:13:06,550 --> 01:13:08,220
Seems natural.

1070
01:13:08,870 --> 01:13:10,620
Even comforting, now.

1071
01:13:12,390 --> 01:13:14,060
You're even teaching me
how to die?

1072
01:13:14,670 --> 01:13:17,660
l'm through teaching you anything.

1073
01:13:19,070 --> 01:13:20,420
You've grown up.

1074
01:13:30,630 --> 01:13:34,060
You can do anything
with your life that you want to.

1075
01:13:35,590 --> 01:13:36,860
What do you mean?

1076
01:13:38,350 --> 01:13:39,860
Figure it out.

1077
01:13:40,550 --> 01:13:42,540
You seen Linda Marolla lately?

1078
01:13:43,310 --> 01:13:44,820
Linda Marolla?

1079
01:13:45,590 --> 01:13:47,230
Why would you ask about her?

1080
01:13:47,430 --> 01:13:50,820
l don't know what l'm talking about.
l'm dying.

1081
01:13:58,390 --> 01:14:00,110
Want me to read you Shakespeare?

1082
01:14:00,350 --> 01:14:03,070
Hamlet was in big trouble
when we left off.

1083
01:14:03,270 --> 01:14:04,380
No.

1084
01:14:19,470 --> 01:14:21,190
You're a good son.

1085
01:15:11,910 --> 01:15:14,790
You take your average kid today.

1086
01:15:15,270 --> 01:15:17,300
He don't want to go in the army.

1087
01:15:17,550 --> 01:15:19,860
Yeah, what does he care? Dope!

1088
01:15:20,070 --> 01:15:23,740
But the Communists,
they go in the army!

1089
01:15:24,430 --> 01:15:26,940
lf only we had some Communists here.

1090
01:15:27,510 --> 01:15:28,740
No.

1091
01:15:30,150 --> 01:15:32,580
While our kids are dancing. . .

1092
01:15:32,950 --> 01:15:35,670
. . .their kids are learning
how to fight!

1093
01:15:35,910 --> 01:15:38,060
Everybody's dancing here!

1094
01:15:38,270 --> 01:15:41,460
You're right. You're right.
lt's not worth talking about.

1095
01:15:41,670 --> 01:15:44,470
-Let me buy you another drink.
-Right.

1096
01:15:44,950 --> 01:15:46,180
What do you do?

1097
01:15:46,790 --> 01:15:48,580
l'm a dance instructor.

1098
01:15:51,270 --> 01:15:54,070
No, l'm kidding. l'm kidding!
Honest to God.

1099
01:15:54,310 --> 01:15:55,260
l'm a dentist.

1100
01:15:55,750 --> 01:15:57,540
l hate dentists.

1101
01:15:58,150 --> 01:16:01,820
We're not bad guys.
lt's not easy, you know.

1102
01:16:02,030 --> 01:16:05,220
There's teeth and gums and blood!

1103
01:16:05,470 --> 01:16:07,060
Oh, my God!

1104
01:16:07,470 --> 01:16:10,110
l have to get looped
just to walk into my office.

1105
01:16:10,350 --> 01:16:13,860
Bartender!
We would like two more, please.

1106
01:16:14,110 --> 01:16:17,070
-Haven't you had enough?
-l want more than enough.

1107
01:16:18,870 --> 01:16:22,380
How come you got all this
money for all these drinks?

1108
01:16:22,710 --> 01:16:26,910
l saved my money.
l haven't had a drink in a month.

1109
01:16:27,110 --> 01:16:28,700
Oh, my God!

1110
01:16:28,950 --> 01:16:31,100
Well, you see, my father died.

1111
01:16:33,630 --> 01:16:35,420
So l stayed sober.

1112
01:16:37,310 --> 01:16:39,140
One night at the hospital. . .

1113
01:16:39,390 --> 01:16:42,060
. . .he fell asleep.
l was watching him.

1114
01:16:43,110 --> 01:16:44,260
And then. . .

1115
01:16:45,310 --> 01:16:47,580
. . .he just kept on sleeping.

1116
01:16:48,750 --> 01:16:50,700
And l was all alone.

1117
01:16:50,910 --> 01:16:52,820
Oh, that's terrible.

1118
01:16:53,710 --> 01:16:55,140
Listen. . .

1119
01:16:55,630 --> 01:16:58,060
. . .l was lucky to know him at all.

1120
01:16:59,350 --> 01:17:00,910
Are you somebody's father?

1121
01:17:01,150 --> 01:17:03,100
No, l'm a drunk.

1122
01:17:03,910 --> 01:17:07,420
l have a brother
who moved to New Jersey.

1123
01:17:08,350 --> 01:17:10,070
l'm getting married soon.

1124
01:17:10,310 --> 01:17:11,460
Great!

1125
01:17:11,670 --> 01:17:13,390
l don't love her.

1126
01:17:14,390 --> 01:17:15,380
l don't love her!

1127
01:17:15,630 --> 01:17:17,110
Well, don't make a scene!

1128
01:17:17,350 --> 01:17:19,580
No, l'm sorry, but there's. . .

1129
01:17:19,830 --> 01:17:21,180
. . .this other girl.

1130
01:17:22,150 --> 01:17:23,710
She steals ties. . .

1131
01:17:25,470 --> 01:17:28,030
. . .and gives them to her father.
She's funny.

1132
01:17:30,350 --> 01:17:31,620
l want her.

1133
01:17:33,510 --> 01:17:34,500
l want her!

1134
01:17:34,710 --> 01:17:35,940
l have to go.

1135
01:17:38,870 --> 01:17:40,100
Sorry.

1136
01:17:40,390 --> 01:17:43,350
Sir, your wedding is within
less than five hours.

1137
01:17:43,830 --> 01:17:44,860
Listen.

1138
01:17:45,110 --> 01:17:47,060
Go see your brother.

1139
01:17:47,310 --> 01:17:48,180
All right?

1140
01:17:48,550 --> 01:17:51,270
Nobody should be alone.

1141
01:17:51,510 --> 01:17:53,300
lt's awful. . .

1142
01:17:53,870 --> 01:17:55,430
. . .to be alone.

1143
01:18:02,350 --> 01:18:05,310
l want you to know, if he doesn't
show up for this wedding. . .

1144
01:18:05,550 --> 01:18:06,460
. . .l'll kill him.

1145
01:18:06,710 --> 01:18:10,590
Don't worry about it, Burt.
l talk to Arthur every day.

1146
01:18:10,830 --> 01:18:13,710
Since Hobson's death, he's stopped
drinking. He's anxious to work.

1147
01:18:14,030 --> 01:18:17,780
He's become a responsible citizen.
He'll be a good husband.

1148
01:18:18,350 --> 01:18:20,460
Thanks very much.
Have a nice day.

1149
01:18:21,710 --> 01:18:24,670
-Where's my roll?
-We're having it monogrammed.

1150
01:18:24,870 --> 01:18:26,820
Hurry up with the old man's roll!

1151
01:18:29,430 --> 01:18:30,300
Can l help you?

1152
01:18:30,550 --> 01:18:32,860
Do you recommend the French toast?

1153
01:18:33,110 --> 01:18:34,510
With all of my heart.

1154
01:18:36,270 --> 01:18:37,750
Lady, l got customers.

1155
01:18:38,230 --> 01:18:39,420
l'll have it.

1156
01:18:39,670 --> 01:18:41,700
You've made the right decision.

1157
01:18:42,030 --> 01:18:43,260
Wait a minute! Wait!

1158
01:18:43,510 --> 01:18:44,940
l've waited long enough.

1159
01:18:46,750 --> 01:18:49,550
Can you take the next
60 years off?

1160
01:18:50,350 --> 01:18:51,780
l'll have to ask.

1161
01:18:55,270 --> 01:18:57,830
-You want some coffee?
-Where's my roll?

1162
01:18:58,070 --> 01:18:59,260
Wait! l'll get it!

1163
01:18:59,510 --> 01:19:02,340
-What the hell's going on?
-She's getting your roll.

1164
01:19:04,270 --> 01:19:05,460
Here's your roll.

1165
01:19:05,710 --> 01:19:06,620
Arthur, what happened?

1166
01:19:06,870 --> 01:19:08,100
Hobson died.

1167
01:19:08,430 --> 01:19:09,380
l know.

1168
01:19:09,630 --> 01:19:12,300
He loved you very much.
Did you know that?

1169
01:19:12,590 --> 01:19:14,900
And l think l'll grow up.

1170
01:19:15,150 --> 01:19:16,340
l want to marry you.

1171
01:19:18,030 --> 01:19:21,140
Although l'm supposed
to marry Susan in 20 minutes.

1172
01:19:21,390 --> 01:19:24,460
-He's drunk, but he sounds sincere.
-Eat your roll!

1173
01:19:26,110 --> 01:19:28,460
The money.
Can you live without the money?

1174
01:19:28,910 --> 01:19:30,500
Well, we'll have to.

1175
01:19:32,950 --> 01:19:34,820
Please marry me.

1176
01:19:36,590 --> 01:19:39,260
l'll try to be sober
and to make you happy.

1177
01:19:39,510 --> 01:19:42,180
Although it won't be easy,
because l'll be poor.

1178
01:19:42,430 --> 01:19:43,300
We'll be poor.

1179
01:19:43,510 --> 01:19:44,580
We'll be poor.

1180
01:19:45,030 --> 01:19:47,500
-Most people are poor.
-Eat your roll!

1181
01:19:47,750 --> 01:19:51,140
Now, l have to tell Susan.
Come with me?

1182
01:19:51,390 --> 01:19:52,380
l got to change.

1183
01:19:52,630 --> 01:19:54,350
-l'll cover for you.
-All right.

1184
01:19:56,150 --> 01:19:58,660
Last night, l could have sworn
the moon was following me.

1185
01:19:58,870 --> 01:20:00,300
lt was.

1186
01:20:27,350 --> 01:20:29,260
l'm Arthur Bach, the groom.

1187
01:20:29,550 --> 01:20:30,950
Congratulations!

1188
01:20:31,190 --> 01:20:33,300
Thank you. And to you too.

1189
01:20:33,550 --> 01:20:36,620
l wonder, could you tell me
where the wedding party is?

1190
01:20:36,830 --> 01:20:38,820
Right over there, in that room.

1191
01:20:39,350 --> 01:20:42,820
Thank you very much.
You've got a lovely. . .

1192
01:20:47,190 --> 01:20:50,020
. . .hat! Hat. lt's called a hat.

1193
01:20:54,790 --> 01:20:55,980
Good luck, Arthur.

1194
01:20:56,990 --> 01:21:00,260
Thank you very much.
l'm Arthur Bach, the groom.

1195
01:21:01,390 --> 01:21:02,660
l'm Arthur Bach.

1196
01:21:11,990 --> 01:21:13,820
Did you forget your garter belt?

1197
01:21:19,510 --> 01:21:20,910
Sorry l'm late.

1198
01:21:24,430 --> 01:21:27,260
Susan, just the one l wanted
to talk to.

1199
01:21:27,510 --> 01:21:28,060
Nice dress.

1200
01:21:28,310 --> 01:21:31,620
-Arthur, the ceremony's just--
-Yeah, l know.

1201
01:21:33,110 --> 01:21:37,020
Could we just talk for a moment,
away from all these people?

1202
01:21:38,310 --> 01:21:39,380
Of course.

1203
01:21:52,910 --> 01:21:55,020
l don't love you. l don't love you.

1204
01:21:55,230 --> 01:21:57,420
-What is it, dear?
-l don't love you.

1205
01:21:58,070 --> 01:21:59,220
l don't love you!

1206
01:21:59,630 --> 01:22:01,420
lt's right in that room over there.

1207
01:22:01,710 --> 01:22:03,620
Thank you.
Your hat is lovely.

1208
01:22:04,270 --> 01:22:05,540
l've heard.

1209
01:22:07,790 --> 01:22:09,220
You're drunk?

1210
01:22:10,230 --> 01:22:11,580
You're frightened?

1211
01:22:11,830 --> 01:22:13,470
l'm both of those.

1212
01:22:13,710 --> 01:22:15,900
l know, but l'm. . .

1213
01:22:16,150 --> 01:22:17,870
. . .in love with another woman.

1214
01:22:18,110 --> 01:22:21,620
-What, dear?
-l'm in love with another woman.

1215
01:22:23,750 --> 01:22:24,860
l'm in love. . .

1216
01:22:25,870 --> 01:22:27,940
. . .with another. . .

1217
01:22:28,190 --> 01:22:29,180
. . .woman!

1218
01:22:30,030 --> 01:22:31,780
Susan, the one innocent. . .

1219
01:22:31,990 --> 01:22:35,220
. . .person in all of this has been you.
l'm really sorry.

1220
01:22:35,430 --> 01:22:37,260
Shut up, Arthur! Just shut up!

1221
01:22:39,190 --> 01:22:40,750
Daddy!

1222
01:22:45,430 --> 01:22:47,340
Hello, Mr. Johnson!

1223
01:22:59,470 --> 01:23:01,190
He must be nervous.

1224
01:23:01,430 --> 01:23:03,020
Arthur gets nervous.

1225
01:23:05,110 --> 01:23:07,460
Here's your ring, Arthur.

1226
01:23:08,710 --> 01:23:10,060
l hope you're happy.

1227
01:23:10,310 --> 01:23:13,620
Now, stand up, son, l want
to kill you with my bare hands.

1228
01:23:15,950 --> 01:23:19,660
l think you know everyone.
This is Susan's father.

1229
01:23:20,150 --> 01:23:21,580
My God! Arthur, you're really hurt!

1230
01:23:23,630 --> 01:23:26,540
l've got him right
where l want him.

1231
01:23:31,470 --> 01:23:33,260
You animal!

1232
01:23:33,510 --> 01:23:34,910
Look, it's over!

1233
01:23:35,230 --> 01:23:38,340
He doesn't love your daughter.
l'm sorry. lt happens.

1234
01:23:38,670 --> 01:23:39,700
He loves me.

1235
01:23:39,910 --> 01:23:41,550
What about Harold?

1236
01:23:42,670 --> 01:23:44,310
Harold?

1237
01:23:44,550 --> 01:23:46,270
-You poor thing.
-Stand aside.

1238
01:23:46,510 --> 01:23:50,340
Now, is this the slut that
you've disgraced my daughter for?!

1239
01:23:50,590 --> 01:23:51,380
Slut?!

1240
01:23:53,110 --> 01:23:54,180
Slut?!

1241
01:24:15,510 --> 01:24:16,380
Please, Daddy!

1242
01:24:16,630 --> 01:24:19,220
-Daddy, he's not worth it.
-Just sit up.

1243
01:24:19,470 --> 01:24:21,060
Can you move, Arthur?

1244
01:24:21,430 --> 01:24:22,660
Everybody out!

1245
01:24:23,630 --> 01:24:25,270
Out! All of you, out!

1246
01:24:28,310 --> 01:24:29,660
God!

1247
01:24:35,190 --> 01:24:38,020
He's taking the knife
out of the cheese!

1248
01:24:39,390 --> 01:24:40,900
Do you think he wants
some cheese?

1249
01:24:41,110 --> 01:24:43,180
No, l think we're going to die!

1250
01:24:50,550 --> 01:24:51,870
What's going on here?

1251
01:24:52,070 --> 01:24:54,020
Stop that this instant!

1252
01:24:55,510 --> 01:24:58,260
Don't screw with me, Burt!

1253
01:25:38,230 --> 01:25:40,140
Ladies and gentlemen. . .

1254
01:25:42,830 --> 01:25:43,980
. . .l'm sorry.

1255
01:25:46,110 --> 01:25:49,660
As you probably have surmised by now. . .

1256
01:25:49,910 --> 01:25:51,740
. . .there will be no wedding.

1257
01:25:53,550 --> 01:25:54,950
The bride. . .

1258
01:25:55,190 --> 01:25:56,910
. . .has had second thoughts. . .

1259
01:25:57,590 --> 01:25:59,340
. . .and has decided. . .

1260
01:25:59,590 --> 01:26:01,020
. . .not to marry me.

1261
01:26:01,270 --> 01:26:04,420
Most of you know me.
Can you blame her?

1262
01:26:08,310 --> 01:26:11,940
l won't be seeing most of you
anymore because. . .

1263
01:26:14,350 --> 01:26:16,420
. . .l'm going to be. . .

1264
01:26:17,710 --> 01:26:18,820
. . .poor.

1265
01:26:22,790 --> 01:26:24,430
l'll miss you.

1266
01:26:29,590 --> 01:26:32,100
Now there's a good. . .

1267
01:26:32,350 --> 01:26:34,180
. . .chance l should go. . .

1268
01:26:35,350 --> 01:26:36,910
. . .to the hospital.

1269
01:26:46,030 --> 01:26:49,260
This has some iodine on it,
so it might hurt a little.

1270
01:26:49,510 --> 01:26:51,620
That hurts, l hate it! Stop it!

1271
01:26:52,870 --> 01:26:56,140
-Why did you do that?
-Because l hate an infection!

1272
01:26:56,910 --> 01:26:59,020
lf you'd have just
let me get--

1273
01:27:06,310 --> 01:27:08,420
Look, as long as we're here. . . .

1274
01:27:08,830 --> 01:27:10,700
Do you promise to love me. . .

1275
01:27:10,950 --> 01:27:12,220
. . .and obey me?

1276
01:27:12,630 --> 01:27:13,860
And be a good boy?

1277
01:27:15,790 --> 01:27:16,620
l do.

1278
01:27:17,310 --> 01:27:21,100
And do you promise never to put
that stuff on my face again?

1279
01:27:21,470 --> 01:27:22,340
l do.

1280
01:27:23,750 --> 01:27:24,780
God!

1281
01:27:25,350 --> 01:27:27,220
We're going to be great!

1282
01:27:28,150 --> 01:27:30,180
We're going to be like. . .

1283
01:27:30,390 --> 01:27:34,620
. . .one of those poor couples
on the subway who hold hands.

1284
01:27:35,230 --> 01:27:37,220
How much is the subway?

1285
01:27:37,710 --> 01:27:40,740
Sixty cents. But if you spit,
it's a $500 fine.

1286
01:27:41,110 --> 01:27:43,140
Then l won't spit.

1287
01:27:43,390 --> 01:27:45,180
Good! None of the best people do.

1288
01:27:45,430 --> 01:27:46,700
l'll get a job!

1289
01:27:47,630 --> 01:27:49,620
That's what l'll do!

1290
01:27:49,870 --> 01:27:51,590
l'll get a job!

1291
01:27:52,510 --> 01:27:53,460
l'll work!

1292
01:27:54,230 --> 01:27:55,630
God, this'll be great!

1293
01:27:55,870 --> 01:27:58,460
-Good! Look how excited he is.
-l'll come home from work.

1294
01:27:58,990 --> 01:28:00,580
You'll be ironing.

1295
01:28:00,830 --> 01:28:03,100
We'll eat some cheap,
disgusting food.

1296
01:28:03,350 --> 01:28:04,220
Stop!

1297
01:28:04,750 --> 01:28:06,470
l think we're in trouble.

1298
01:28:06,710 --> 01:28:08,900
That is out of the question!

1299
01:28:10,190 --> 01:28:13,540
There has never been such a thing
as a working-class Bach!

1300
01:28:14,390 --> 01:28:16,460
And there never will be!

1301
01:28:19,310 --> 01:28:21,420
Step! Step!

1302
01:28:23,270 --> 01:28:24,700
l've reached a decision.

1303
01:28:25,070 --> 01:28:29,820
The Bach family must endure.
And not on a subway.

1304
01:28:30,270 --> 01:28:33,020
Your children will be
senators, ambassadors.

1305
01:28:33,270 --> 01:28:35,620
Perhaps even a president!

1306
01:28:36,670 --> 01:28:40,220
You have your 750 million dollars.

1307
01:28:40,990 --> 01:28:42,220
All right!

1308
01:28:46,110 --> 01:28:47,860
l don't know, Martha.

1309
01:28:48,750 --> 01:28:50,180
You don't know?!

1310
01:28:50,430 --> 01:28:53,310
-Money has screwed me up my whole life.
-l know!

1311
01:28:53,590 --> 01:28:56,060
l've always been rich
and never been happy.

1312
01:28:56,310 --> 01:28:58,460
l've always been poor
and usually been happy.

1313
01:28:58,710 --> 01:29:02,420
Rubbish! l've always been rich
and l've always been happy.

1314
01:29:04,470 --> 01:29:07,430
Would you make me
a tuna fish sandwich?

1315
01:29:08,750 --> 01:29:11,420
l'm going to have
a tuna fish sandwich, Martha.

1316
01:29:11,670 --> 01:29:12,820
Step.

1317
01:29:17,270 --> 01:29:20,230
l demand that you take this money.

1318
01:29:21,550 --> 01:29:23,820
l want a decision
and l want it now!

1319
01:29:25,430 --> 01:29:29,020
l can't tell you what a lousy
wedding that was, Bitterman.

1320
01:29:31,470 --> 01:29:33,380
Bitterman, goodbye.

1321
01:29:34,390 --> 01:29:35,460
l'm going.

1322
01:29:36,110 --> 01:29:37,540
Goodbye, sir.

1323
01:29:37,790 --> 01:29:39,980
lt was a pleasure working for you.

1324
01:29:40,230 --> 01:29:42,740
Chauffeurs rarely get to laugh.
Thank you.

1325
01:29:42,990 --> 01:29:44,980
-Goodbye, Bitterman.
-Goodbye, miss.

1326
01:29:45,190 --> 01:29:48,580
Arthur, l'm going!
Open that door, Rockland!

1327
01:29:49,870 --> 01:29:52,860
-Ever been on a yacht?
-No, is it wonderful?

1328
01:29:53,110 --> 01:29:55,020
lt doesn't suck.

1329
01:29:55,390 --> 01:29:58,580
l shall never offer you
this money again.

1330
01:29:59,510 --> 01:30:02,260
l wish you luck in your poverty.

1331
01:30:07,110 --> 01:30:08,260
Excuse me.

1332
01:30:28,230 --> 01:30:29,380
What happened?

1333
01:30:29,630 --> 01:30:30,980
l turned her down.

1334
01:30:32,070 --> 01:30:34,220
She invited us for dinner
and l said. . .

1335
01:30:34,430 --> 01:30:37,540
. . .we're having a tuna fish sandwich.
So l turned her down.

1336
01:30:38,670 --> 01:30:41,420
l took the money, l mean,
l'm not crazy!

1337
01:30:43,790 --> 01:30:45,430
Do you want to double your salary?

1338
01:30:45,710 --> 01:30:47,900
-Then open that door.
-Right away, sir.

1339
01:30:48,150 --> 01:30:49,420
ls that funny?

1340
01:30:51,950 --> 01:30:52,900
Where to, sir?

1341
01:30:54,190 --> 01:30:58,260
The park. Drive through the park.
You know how l love the park.

1342
01:30:58,510 --> 01:31:00,580
-Get in! Step!
-Step!

1343
01:31:02,030 --> 01:31:04,500
ARTHUR
NEW YORK

